        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 3:22PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 322 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Minturn, or 7 miles southwest of Hoxie, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Walnut Ridge...                   Hoxie...
College City...                   Alicia...
Minturn...                        Sedgwick...
Strangers Home...                 Giles Spur...
Lauratown...                      Clover Bend...
Calvin...                         Dicus...
Coffman...                        Arbor Grove...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
